A photo of Meghan Cremer taken from her Facebook account. JOHANNESBURG - Three men appeared briefly in the Athlone Magistrate's Court on Thursday morning, in connection with the abduction and murder of Cape Town horse rider Meghan Cremer. The men, aged between 27 and 35, were arrested several hours after she went missing on Saturday evening. According to Netwerk24, one of the suspects led police to a sand mine in Philippi in the early hours of Thursday morning, where 30-year-old Cremer's body was found in a shallow grave. It's reported that her hands were tied and she had a rope around her neck. READ: Mother discovers child's body in a pile of garbage "Police charged the three with illegal possession of a presumably stolen vehicle," said Police Spokesperson, FC Van Wyk. The men were remanded in custody and the case was postponed to 15 August.